    "voiceover_text": "Hey girlies, I'm Muneera from Namshe Fashion Team and I'm here with Dossier looking at their new perfume. So they've got new Lost Americana and Ambery Saffron. Now I'm not normally a saffron girl, but let's give this a try. It really smells so luxurious and reminds me of MFK's Booker at Rouge. We've got the It Factor, that is both ginger, brown sugar, and sandalwood, and I do love a sandalwood scent. And then there's Ambery Vanilla. It's so sophisticated. If you love YSL's Black Opium, then you're really going to enjoy it. Then we have Lost Americana. Now this has been a collaboration with MGK and what I really love about this is that the price point is really affordable, so everyone can smell good, especially in time for Ramadan. Incense, top notes, middle notes are nutmeg, myrrh, and pepper. I mean, I don't know what love smells like. Almond, love, and pink cinnamon, and the base notes are Vivita, patchouli, suede, vanilla, and chocolate. Darn, if anyone's looking for a gift from me, why not just take this?",
